## Part 1 — Technical Spec

### 1.1 Data Source

**View:** `vw_ae_stage_context`

This view joins `ae_assessments` and `ae_backend_stage_ref_table` and returns a flat payload containing all content needed to render the full tab. It also includes five static ladder overview fields — one per frontend stage — so the full five-rung ladder overview at the top of the tab renders from the same single query.

| Field Group | Source |
|---|---|
| Assessment identity | `ae_assessments` |
| Current sub-stage content | `ae_backend_stage_ref_table` (joined on `ae_backend_stage_id`) |
| Five-stage ladder overview | Five static joins to canonical mid-stage rows |

---

### 1.2 Tab Section Map

The tab is structured into five sections rendered in order. None of the sections are expandable — all content is always visible. The tab is intentionally compact.

---

#### SECTION 1 — The Agency Engine Ladder (Framework Overview)

**Purpose:** Orient the founder in the full five-stage model before showing their specific position. This is the same for all users regardless of stage.

**Layout:** A brief intro paragraph followed by a five-stage visual ladder — each rung showing the stage name and its one-liner description.

| UI Element | View Field | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Intro heading | Static: "The Agency Engine (AE) Ladder" | Hard-coded string |
| Intro paragraph | Static | Hard-coded: "The AE Ladder is the roadmap for agency maturity, defining the 5 stages of evolution: Rising, Striving, Thriving, Driving, and Arriving. Understanding your stage is the first step to unlocking the next level of growth." |
| Rising rung label | Static: "Rising" | |
| Rising rung description | `ladder_rising_description` | `ae_stage_description_short` from `ae_bk_stg_1` |
| Striving rung label | Static: "Striving" | |
| Striving rung description | `ladder_striving_description` | `ae_stage_description_short` from `ae_bk_stg_4` |
| Thriving rung label | Static: "Thriving" | |
| Thriving rung description | `ladder_thriving_description` | `ae_stage_description_short` from `ae_bk_stg_7` |
| Driving rung label | Static: "Driving" | |
| Driving rung description | `ladder_driving_description` | `ae_stage_description_short` from `ae_bk_stg_10` |
| Arriving rung label | Static: "Arriving" | |
| Arriving rung description | `ladder_arriving_description` | `ae_stage_description_short` from `ae_bk_stg_11` (proxy until Arriving row exists) |
| Active stage highlight | `ae_frontend_stage` | Visually highlight the user's current stage on the ladder |

**Rendering notes:**
- The user's current frontend stage should be visually distinguished on the ladder — highlighted, bolded, or marked with an indicator
- The ladder is display-only — no click or interaction needed on individual rungs

