#### SECTION 3 — Where You Sit Within This Stage

**Purpose:** Show the founder their precise sub-stage position — whether they're early in the stage, in the core, or approaching the transition to the next stage. This is the personalization layer.

**Layout:** Two side-by-side cards — Key Themes and Journey Context.

**Sub-stage position label:**

| UI Element | View Field | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Position label | `ae_backend_stage` | The sub-stage name e.g. "Early Striving", "Striving → Thriving Transition" |
| Short description | `ae_stage_description_short` | One-liner below the position label |

**Key Themes card:**

| UI Element | View Field | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Card heading | Static: "Key Themes at This Stage" | |
| Theme bullets | `stage_key_themes` | JSONB array — render each item as a bullet point |

**Journey Context card:**

| UI Element | View Field | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Card heading | Static: "Your Journey Context" | |
| Context paragraph | `next_stage_description` | Describes what moving toward the next stage looks and requires |
| Pull quote | `stage_transition_quote` | Rendered in italics below the paragraph |

**Rendering notes:**
- `stage_key_themes` is a JSONB array — parse and render each string as a bullet item
- If `stage_key_themes` is null (content not yet loaded), render a neutral placeholder: `"Stage themes loading..."` rather than an empty card
- If `stage_transition_quote` is null, omit the pull quote entirely — do not render empty italics

---

#### SECTION 4 — Your Next Growth Milestone

**Purpose:** Preview what the next stage looks like so the founder understands what they are working toward.

| UI Element | View Field | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Section heading | Static: "Your Next Growth Milestone" |  |
| Next stage label | `next_ae_stage` | Displayed as: "Stage: [next_ae_stage]" |
| Next stage tagline | `ae_next_stage_tagline` | Sub-headline |
| Next stage description | `next_stage_description` | Full paragraph — same field as Journey Context above, used again here in a different layout context |

**Rendering notes:**
- If the user is at the Arriving stage (highest stage), this section should render a completion message instead: "You've reached the top of the AE Ladder. The focus now is on optionality, durability, and intentional evolution." Hide the next stage fields gracefully.
- `next_ae_stage` will be null for Arriving-stage users — use this as the conditional flag

---

#### SECTION 5 — CTA Block

**Purpose:** Direct the founder to the Maturity & Readiness Audit as the clear next action. Tier-aware copy — same destination, different framing based on access level.

**Layout:** Dark background block at the bottom of the tab. Heading, supporting copy, one primary CTA button, one secondary resource link.

| UI Element | Source | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Block heading | Static: "Ready to Map Your Next Move?" | Hard-coded |
| Supporting copy — Free / Tier 1 users | Static | "You know your stage. The Maturity & Readiness Audit goes deeper — mapping exactly what needs attention, in what order, to reach your next level." |
| Supporting copy — Pro / Coaching users | Static | "Your stage is set. The Maturity & Readiness Audit is your next step — a full diagnostic of where to focus and what to build first." |
| CTA button — Free / Tier 1 | Static | Label: "Get the Full Diagnostic" → links to M&R Audit upgrade or purchase page |
| CTA button — Pro / Coaching | Static | Label: "Take the Maturity & Readiness Audit" → links to M&R Audit intake within the platform |
| CTA supporting line | `ae_stage_cta_tagline` | Displayed in smaller text beneath the button |
| Secondary link | `field_guide_url` | Label: "Download Your [Stage] Field Guide" — only shown if `field_guide_url` is not null |

**Tier detection logic:**
- Check the user's current access tier from the auth/profile context already available in the dashboard
- Tier 0 (Free) and Tier 1 (AE Ladder Snapshot) → show upgrade-framed CTA copy
- Tier 2 (Full Diagnostic), Tier 3 (Pro), or Coaching → show action-framed CTA copy
- If tier cannot be determined, default to the upgrade-framed version

