## Part 3 — Content Population Sequence

The tab build can proceed in parallel with content population since null states are handled throughout. The sequence for content readiness is:

1. Run the Stage Context SQL script to add columns and create the view
2. Run the content extraction prompt with all five Field Guide PDFs and framework reference docs
3. Review and approve the returned JSON
4. Run the 11 UPDATE statements to populate `stage_key_themes`, `stage_transition_quote`, and `field_guide_url` for all rows
5. Upload the Field Guide PDFs to Supabase Storage or equivalent and replace `PENDING_[STAGE]` placeholder values with real signed or public URLs
6. Re-verify the view returns fully populated data for the test assessment

Once content population is complete, the tab will render with full content automatically — no additional code changes needed.

